Rule: Higher education levels (Masters, Doctorate, Prof-school) compared to HS-grad significantly increase the likelihood of earning more than 50k $ a year.
Being married or widowed, as opposed to being single, increases the likelihood of earning more than 50k $ a year.
Having a "Professional" occupation increases the likelihood of earning more than 50k $ a year.
Being self-employed increases the likelihood of earning more than 50k $ a year compared to being employed in the private sector.
